# Project Conventions

Follow all conventions defined in @AGENTS.md.

## Cursor-Specific

### Composer Usage
- Use Composer (Cmd/Ctrl+I) for multi-file changes
- Review all proposed changes before accepting
- Accept/reject changes per file when appropriate

### Context References
- Use `@codebase` for project-wide questions
- Use `@filename` for specific file context
- Use `@docs` to reference documentation

### Inline Editing
- Use Cmd/Ctrl+K for quick inline changes
- Be specific about the change needed
- Review diff before accepting

## Code Style Reminders

### TypeScript
- Strict mode - no `any` types
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- Use interfaces for object shapes

### React Components
```typescript
// Component structure
interface Props {
  title: string;
  onAction?: () => void;
}

export function MyComponent({ title, onAction }: Props) {
  return <div>{title}</div>;
}
```

### Error Handling
```typescript
// API calls
try {
  const result = await api.fetchData();
  return { success: true, data: result };
} catch (error) {
  logger.error('Failed to fetch data', { error });
  throw new ApiError(500, 'Failed to fetch data');
}
```

## Testing Conventions

- Tests live next to implementation
- Name: `component-name.test.tsx`
- Use React Testing Library
- Test behavior, not implementation
